name: vue-pdf-viewer-examples
description: This repository contains examples of Syncfusion PDF Viewer (Web) control.

name: vue3-treemap-getting-started
description: Learn here all about Getting Started with Syncfusion TreeMap in Vue application using Vue CLI.

name: vue3-maps-getting-started
description: Learn here all about Getting Started with Syncfusion Maps in Vue application using Vue CLI.

name: getting-started-with-the-vue-barcode-and-qrcode-generator
description: A quick-start project that shows how to add the Syncfusion Barcode and QR Code Generator components to a Vue application. This project contains the code to generate different barcode types, QR code and data matrix, and how to customize the control like changing its dimensions, color, and font.

name: getting-started-with-the-vue-speed-dial-component
description: A quick start Vue project that shows how to add the Vue Speed Dial component to a Vue application. It shows how to integrate the speed dial into the vue grid. It also shows how to customize the position, direction and display mode of the speed dial.

name: getting-started-with-the-vue-color-picker-component
description: A quick start Vue project that shows how to add the Vue ColorPicker component to a Vue application. It shows how to set a value, change the display mode, disable the switcher mode and customize the palette with user-defined colors. It also shows how to hide the control buttons and input area in the component.

name: getting-started-with-the-vue-button-component
description: A quick start Vue project that shows how to add the Vue Button component to a Vue application. It shows how to display and position icons in the Button. It also shows how to change the button types and customize the styles.

name: How-to-Create-Stacked-Headers-in-the-Vue-Kanban-Component
description: A quick-start Vue project that shows how to create stacked headers in the Vue Kanban component. It includes a code snippet for adding stacked headers, making columns collapsible, and setting columns to a collapsed state by default.

name: how-to-load-tab-items-from-a-remote-data-source-in-vue-tabs
description: A quick start Vue project that shows how to bind JSON and Remote data sources to the Vue Tab Component.

name: Integrating-Syncfusion-Vue-components-to-the-Astro-application
description: This repository contains the Syncfusion Rich Text Editor component example using the Astro application.

name: getting-started-with-the-vue-dropdown-menu-component
description: A quick start Vue project that shows how to add the Vue Dropdown Menu component to a Vue application. It shows how to add separators and display icons in the Dropdown Menu. It also shows how to navigate to the other web page when an action item is clicked.

name: getting-started-with-the-vue-rich-text-editor-component
description: A quick start Vue project that shows how to add the Vue Rich Text Editor Component to a Vue application. It includes a code snippet for adding the desired toolbar items to the toolbar and adding the HTML elements like table, image and link to the component.

name: getting-started-with-the-vue-kanban-component
description: A quick start Vue project that shows how to add the Vue Kanban Component to a Vue application. It includes a code snippet for binding data from the remote data source, enabling swimlane feature, and setting custom height and width. It also includes a code snippet for adding a tooltip and validate columns.

name: how-to-integrate-the-mention-component-and-third-party-libraries-in-vue-RTE
description: A quick start Vue project that shows how to integrate the mention component and the third-party libraries in the Vue rich text editor component

name: how-to-add-a-custom-tool-to-the-vue-rich-text-editor-component
description: A quick start Vue project that shows how to add a custom tool to the Vue Rich Text Editor component. It shows how to add a custom tool omega and displays a list of special characters in a dialog. It also explains how to insert the special character in the Rich Text Editor

name: how-to-customize-the-pivot-chart-in-a-vue-pivot-table
description: A quick start Vue project that shows how to display a pivot chart in the Vue Pivot Table Component. This project includes a code snippet for customizing the axes, data labels, legends and displaying the accumulation charts.

name: how-to-filter-and-sort-data-in-the-vue-pivottable-component
description: A quick start Vue project that shows how to filter and sort data in the Pivot Table component.  This project includes a code snippet for different types of filtering like label and value filtering, and different types of sorting like alphanumeric and value sorting.

name: getting-started-with-the-vue-floating-action-button-component
description: A quick start Vue project that shows how to add the Vue Floating Action Button component to a Vue application. It shows how to integrate the floating action button into the vue ListView. It also shows how to display and customize the position of an icon, and customize the CSS styles.

name: getting-started-with-the-vue-pivottable-component
description: A quick start Vue project that shows how to get started with the Pivot Table component.  This project includes a code snippet to create a new vue application and add Syncfusion Vue Pivot Table component to it. It also includes a code snippet to bind data to the pivot table from a data source and some of its key features.
